title: Static Analysis

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION.description: Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.USE_FINGERPRINT.description: This constant was deprecated in API level 28. Applications should request USE_BIOMETRIC instead

android.permission.READ_CALENDAR.description: Allows an application to read all of the calendar events stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to send your calendar events to other people.

android.permission.WRITE_CALENDAR.info: add or modify calendar events and send emails to guests
android.permission.WRITE_CALENDAR.description: Allows an application to add or change the events on your calendar, which may send emails to guests. Malicious applications can use this to erase or modify your calendar events or to send emails to guests.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to the SD card.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE.description: Allows an application to read from SD Card.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_ADMIN.description: Allows an application to configure the local Bluetooth phone and to discover and pair with remote devices.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH.description: Allows an application to view configuration of the local Bluetooth phone and to make and accept connections with paired devices.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

"fso_more_info" : "Your %1$s

"fso_more_info_ios" : "

For your convenience, we offer several convenient refueling options:

Avis Fuel Service Option:
Save yourself time and frustration by adding our Fuel Service Option to your next online reservation. By selecting the Fuel Service Option, you can purchase a tank of gas directly from Avis at the time of rental, and avoid the hassle of searching for a gas station to fill the tank before returning the car.

If the Fuel Service Option isn't exactly what you're looking for, choose one of the following refueling options at the time of rental:

Self-Service Refueling:
Purchase fuel just prior to returning and return the car to Avis with a full tank of gas. If you choose this option, Avis will not charge you for fuel.

EZFuel and Fuel Service Charge:
Driving under 75 miles? With our newest refueling service, customers who drive less than 75 miles pay a low flat fee for fuel and return the car without refueling. We'll automatically charge you a flat fee of $13.99. If you present a receipt for the purchase of fuel, the charge will be removed at the time of return.

Please Note: Only the Fuel Service Option can be reserved online. Please select FSO on our Rental Options page. If you do not select the Fuel Service Option during your online reservation, you may choose a refueling option at the time of rental.

"

"more_info_debit_card_ios" : "Please spend a moment reviewing these important terms because Avis wants you to be delighted with your rental experience!

A reservation payment on Avis.com is a real-time transaction. Once you accept the terms and conditions, the card that is used to prepay this reservation will be immediately pre-authorized for the full amount of the estimated total charges along with a security deposit. Any unused funds secured on your credit or debit card will be released when you return the car and could take up to 10 business days to appear on your bank statement.

At the time of rental you will be required to present either the credit card or debit card used to make the â€œPay Nowâ€ reservation. There are certain restrictions on the use of the debit card for qualification to rent. Most U.S. locations will accept bank debit cards with the Visa or Mastercard logo if you are at least 25 years of age. At airport locations proof of a return flight that coincides with the rental must be shown. Debit cards are also not accepted when renting specialty vehicles. In most cases U.S. locations will perform a credit check for debit card renters to determine credit worthiness at the time of rental. If we are unable to complete the credit check or the credit check fails you should be prepared to present a major credit card in your own name.

Please Note: Debit cards may not be accepted at some Avis locations.

  • Credit & Debit Card Requirements
  • What To Bring With You At the Rental Counter & What to Expect
  • For Visitors Outside of US & Canada

Please Note: Once your credit information is entered and the reservation is confirmed, you cannot modify this card information."

"roadside_safetynet_more_info_ios" : "

The Avis Extended Roadside Assistance product provides the added reassurance of having roadside service for items that are not normally included in the cost of a rental such as key replacement, fuel delivery, lock out service, jump start assistance or tire change service.

A customer that accepts Extended Roadside Assistance can be assured that all of these services will be covered at no additional fee should they be needed. For example, if keys are locked in the car, Avis will provide the customer with a locksmith service to regain entry at no additional cost to the customer. In the event the customer has a dead battery, a service provider will be dispatched to assist at no additional cost to the customer.

Extended Roadside Assistance Terms & Conditions:

Taxes not included in the Estimated Total and will be applied at the time of rental. Extended Roadside Assistance (ERA) service is available at all participating Avis locations in the U.S., Canada, Puerto Rico & U.S. Virgin Islands and New Zealand. The daily/weekly fee for the AVIS Extended Roadside Assistance Option is subject to change. ERA covers the cost for assistance with key replacement lockouts, tire change service fee, jump starts and emergency fuel delivery (up to 3 gallons). Prohibited use of the vehicle will void this option. A customer that accepts Extended Roadside Assistance can be reassured that all of these service will be covered at no additional fee should they be needed. "sli_more_info_us_ios" : "

Supplemental Liability Insurance (SLI) is excess automobile liability coverage that protects all authorized drivers of the rental vehicle against third-party bodily injury and property-damage claims up to a combined single limit of USD $1,000,000 or $2,000,000 depending on the rental location*. At some locations in states that do not require the car rental company to provide statutory minimum liability coverage, Supplemental Liability Insurance (SLI) will provide automobile liability coverage in excess of the State statutory minimums or your existing liability insurance coverage (whichever is greater), and it protects all authorized drivers of the rental vehicle against third-party bodily injury and property-damage claims up to USD $1,000,000 for your rental in the U.S.(excluding your injuries and your passengers' injuries) arising from your rental. Extra coverage means greater peace of mind. Next time you rent a car, be sure you're prepared for life's unexpected turns. This optional coverage offers you big peace of mind for a small investment.

* If you are renting in California or Nevada, please check with the Budget location for specific carrier, program terms/conditions, exclusions and/or limitations of coverage as these may differ from the SLI described above. We also advise you to consult with your individual insurer before rental.

Subject to the Avis Terms and Conditions.

* Pre-selected Options

If an option is checked and you can't deselect, then either: 1. You chose to include this option with your reservations when you selected your preferences in your RapidRez profile. If you want different protections for this reservation, you'll need to re-start this reservation. You can change your preferences online at any time and those preferences will automatically be applied to your future reservations. Or, 2. The option is included in the car rate that you selected.

"

"txt_css_weight_val" : "


Child Safety Seats Weight Guide

* Child Infant Seat (CIS) : 2-20 lbs or 2.27-9.07 kilos.
* Child Safety Seat (CSS) :  20-40 lbs or 9.07-18.16 kilos.
* Child Booster Seats (CBS) : 40-80 lbs or 18.16-36.32 kilos.


Child Safety Seat Installation Guide

Rear Facing Infant ( Up to 1 year old)
1. Rear Facing
2. Seat Level/Back at 45º angle
3. Latch position (use latch belt)
4. Should not move more than 1"
5. Not in airbag position
6. Only anchors for seat position
7. Not in front of fold down armrest
8. No belt twisted
9. Tether rolled up/secure*
10. Kickstand up and under seat*
11. Proper belt path used*
12. Harness straps two bottom slots*
13. Handle rotated down*
 
 *May not apply to all seats

Check Child
* Harness at or below shoulders
* No more than 2 fingers slack
* Harness clip at armpit level
* Hard not falling forward
* Suggest rolled blanket
 
Forward Facing Convertible Over 1 year old, 20-40LBS (9-18KGS.)
1. Proper belt path
2. Harness straps top slots only
3. Latch position (use latch belt)
4. Should not move more than 1"
5. Tether strap/secured
6. Not in airbag position
7. Secure Choice kickstand locked Tribute kickstand under back of seat
8. No belt twisted
 
Check Child
* Harness at or above shoulders
* No more than 2 fingers slack
* Harness clip at armpit level
 
Booster Check Up to 8 years old, 40-80LBS (13.6-36KGS)
1. Top of ears below top of seat
2. Lap belt across the hips not belly
3. Shoulder strap across collarbone
4. Remind parent to check every time
 
Check Child
* Harness at or above shoulders
* No more than 2 fingers slack
* Harness clip at armpit level

"txt_tems_and_condition_desc_android" : "Opt-in
Avis Mobile Notifications is a standard rated subscription alert service providing time-sensitive mobile alerts to customers that include updates to current/upcoming rentals, promotional offers, MMS and coupons about Avis. By signing up you agree to receive text messages regarding your rental status. We do not, but could, use an automatic telephone dialing system to deliver our text messages. Consent is not required to purchase goods or services.

Opt-out
To Opt-Out (discontinue service), text "STOP" to "48400" from your mobile device. You will not receive any additional text messages. You may also Opt-out by texting "QUIT", "END", "CANCEL", "UNSUBSCRIBE", or "STOP ALL" to any text message you receive or to short code 48400. You can also manage your text messages by updating your Avis profile at Avis.com. Simply select "No" from the SMS Notifications option in the communication preference section of your profile.

Help
To get help, text "HELP" to "48400" or email custserv@avis.com or call 1-800-352-7900

"fso_more_info" : "Votre %1$s

Pour votre commodité, nous offrons plusieurs options commodes de plein d'essence :

Avis Fuel Service Option:
gagnez du temps et épargnez-vous des frustrations en ajoutant notre Option carburant lors de votre prochaine réservation en ligne. En choisissant l'Option carburant, vous pouvez acheter un plein d'essence directement auprès d'Avis au moment de la location et ainsi éviter d'avoir à chercher une station-service pour remplir le réservoir avant de restituer le véhicule.

If the Fuel Service Option isn't exactly what you're looking for, choose one of the following refueling options at the time of rental:

Self-Service Refueling:
Si vous choisissez cette option, vous devrez acheter de l'essence juste avant la restitution du véhicule et remettre le véhicule à Avis avec un réservoir plein. Si vous choisissez cette option, Avis ne vous facturera pas d'essence.

EZFuel and Fuel Service Charge:
Vous conduisez moins de 120 kilomètres? Notre toute nouvelle option de plein d'essence offre à nos clients qui ont moins de 120 kilomètres à faire la possibilité d'acheter un forfait modique pour l'essence et de rendre la voiture sans refaire le plein. Nous vous demanderons automatiquement un paiement forfaitaire de 13,99 $. Si vous présentez un reçu d'achat de carburant, la facturation sera supprimée au moment de la restitution.

Remarque : Seule l'Option carburant peut être réservée en ligne. Veuillez sélectionner l'Option carburant (FSO) sur votre page des options de location. Si vous ne sélectionnez pas l'Option carburant lors de votre réservation en ligne, vous pourrez choisir une option de plein d'essence au moment de la location."

"more_infor_debit_card_andorid" : "Veuillez prendre le temps de revoir ces importantes modalités puisqu'Avis souhaite que vous soyez complètement satisfait de votre expérience de location!

Le paiement d'une réservation sur avis.com est une transaction en temps réel. Une fois les Modalités et conditions acceptées, la carte utilisée pour prépayer cette réservation sera immédiatement préautorisée pour le montant complet de l'estimation des frais de location de même qu'un dépôt de sécurité. Tous les fonds non utilisés débités sur votre carte de débit ou de crédit seront retournés lors de la restitution de la voiture, et cela peut prendre jusqu'à dix jours ouvrables avant d'apparaître sur votre relevé.

Au moment de la location, vous devez présenter la carte de crédit ou de débit utilisée pour faire la réservation « Payer maintenant ». Il y a certaines restrictions sur l'utilisation de la carte de débit pour l'admissibilité de location. À titre d'identification du crédit au moment de la location, la plupart des établissements des États-Unis acceptent également les cartes de débit arborant le logo Visa ou MasterCard, si vous êtes âgé d'au moins 25 ans. Aux succursales d'aéroport, il faut présenter un vol de retour qui coïncide avec la location. Les cartes de débit ne sont pas acceptées lors de la location d'un véhicule spécial. Dans la plupart des cas, les succursales des États-Unis exécuteront une vérification du crédit pour les locataires payant par carte de crédit, afin de déterminer leur solvabilité au moment de la location. Si nous ne sommes pas en mesure de contrôler votre crédit ou si le contrôle du crédit échoue, vous devez être prêt à présenter une des principales cartes de crédit, à votre nom.

Veuillez noter : Certaines succursales Avis peuvent ne pas accepter les cartes de débit.

• Conditions relatives aux cartes de crédit/débit
• Ce dont vous aurez besoin au comptoir de location et Ce à quoi s'attendre

"roadside_safetynet_more_info" : "Votre %1$s

L'assistance routière étendue d'Avis offre l'assurance d'avoir un service routier pour les articles qui ne sont généralement pas inclus dans le coût de la location comme le remplacement de clé, la livraison de carburant, le service de verrouillage, le service de dépannage ou de changement de pneu.

Un client qui accepte l'assistance routière peut être assuré que tous ces services seront couverts sans frais s'il en a besoin. Par exemple, si les clés sont verrouillées dans la voiture, Avis offrira au client les services d'un serrurier pour avoir l'entrée sans coût additionnel au client. Dans le cas où un client a une batterie à plat, un fournisseur sera envoyé afin de l'assister sans frais additionnels pour le client.

Modalités et conditions de l'assistance routière étendue  & Modalités :
:Les taxes ne sont pas comprises dans le total des frais estimés; elles seront imputées au moment de la location.
Le service d'assistance routière étendue est disponible dans toutes les succursales participantes aux États-Unis, au Canada à Porto Rico&, aux îles Vierges américaines et en Nouvelle-Zélande.
Les frais quotidiens/hebdomadaires pour l'option d'assistance routière étendue d'AVIS sont modifiables.
ERA couvre les coûts pour l'assistance pour le remplacement de clé, verrouillage, les frais de service de changement de pneus, démarrage par batterie d'appoint et livraison de carburant en cas d'urgence (jusqu'à 3 gallons).
L'utilisation interdite du véhicule annulera cette option."

Guide de poids des sièges de sécurité pour enfants
* Siège pour enfant (CIS): 2-20 lb ou 2,27-9,07 kilos.
* Siège de sécurité pour enfants (CSS): 20-40 lbs ou 9.07-18.16 kilos.
* Sièges d'appoint pour enfants (CBS): 40 à 80 lb ou 18,16 à 36,32 kilos.

Guide d'installation des sièges de sécurité pour enfants

Nourrisson à l'arrière (jusqu'à 1 an)
1. Face arrière
2. Niveau du siège / Retour à un angle de 45º
3. Position du loquet (utiliser la ceinture de verrouillage)
4. Ne devrait pas bouger plus de 1 "
5. Pas en position airbag
6. Seuls les ancrages pour la position du siège
7. Pas devant l'accoudoir rabattable
8. Aucune courroie tordue
9. Tether enroulé / sécurisé *
10. Kickstand up et under seat *
11. Chemin de courroie approprié utilisé *
12. Harnais sangle deux fentes inférieures *
13. Poignée tournée vers le bas *

* Peut ne pas s'appliquer à toutes les places

Vérifiez l'enfant
* Harnais à ou sous les épaules
* Pas plus de 2 doigts relâchés
* Attache de harnais au niveau des aisselles
* Difficile de ne pas tomber en avant
* Suggérer une couverture roulée

Convertible vers l'avantPlus d'un an, 20-40LBS (9-18KGS.)
1. Chemin de ceinture approprié
2. Harnais sangles supérieures uniquement
3. Position du loquet (utiliser la ceinture de verrouillage)
4. Ne devrait pas bouger plus de 1 "
5. Courroie d'attache / sécurisée
6. Pas en position airbag
7. Béquille Secure Choice verrouillée
8. Aucune courroie tordue

Vérifiez l'enfant
* Harnais à ou au-dessus des épaules
* Pas plus de 2 doigts relâchés
* Attache de harnais au niveau des aisselles

Booster CheckUp jusqu'à 8 ans, 40-80LBS (13.6-36KGS)
1. Haut des oreilles sous le haut du siège
2. Ceinture abdominale sur les hanches, pas le ventre
3. Bandoulière sur la clavicule
4. Rappelez au parent de vérifier à chaque fois

Vérifiez l'enfant
* Harnais à ou au-dessus des épaules
* Pas plus de 2 doigts relâchés
* Attache de harnais au niveau des aisselles

"txt_tems_and_condition_desc_android" : "Abonnement
Avis Mobile Notifications est un service d'abonnement d'alerte à taux standard qui envoie des alertes mobiles sensibles au temps aux clients qui comprennent des mises à jour aux locations actuelles/à venir, des offres promotionnelles, des MMS et des coupons. En vous abonnant, vous convenez de recevoir des messages texte concernant votre statut de location. Nous n'utilisons pas, mais nous pouvons utiliser, un système de composition automatique pour livrer nos messages texte. Le consentement n'est pas nécessaire pour acheter des marchandises ou des services.

Désabonnement
Pour vous désabonner (arrêter le service), envoyer le message texte « STOP » au « 48400 » à partir de votre appareil mobile. Vous ne recevrez plus de messages texte. Vous pouvez également vous désabonner en envoyant le message texte « QUIT », « END », « CANCEL », « UNSUBSCRIBE » ou « STOP ALL » à partir de tout message texte que vous recevez ou au code court 48400. Vous pouvez également gérer vos messages texte en mettant à jour votre profil Avis sur Avis.com. Sélectionnez simplement « No » dans l'option SMS Notifications dans la section de préférence de communication de votre profil.

Aide
Pour obtenir de l'aide, envoyez le texte « HELP » au « 48400 », ou envoyez un courriel à custserv@avis.com, ou appelez le 1 800 352-7900

Garantie
Avis Budget Group n'assumera aucune responsabilité des messages SMS retardés liés à notre passerelle SMS. La livraison des messages SMS est soumise à la transmission efficace à partir de votre fournisseur de service sans fil/opérateur de réseau.

Confidentialité
Nous utiliserons vos renseignements uniquement pour vous fournir les services que vous demandez et ceux indiqués dans notre avis de confidentialité qui se trouve à l'adresse www.avis.com/privacy.

"fso_more_info" : "Your %1$s

For your convenience, we offer several convenient refueling options:

Avis Fuel Service Option:
Save yourself time and frustration by adding our Fuel Service Option to your next online reservation. By selecting the Fuel Service Option, you can purchase a tank of gas directly from Avis at the time of rental, and avoid the hassle of searching for a gas station to fill the tank before returning the car.

If the Fuel Service Option isn’t exactly what you’re looking for, choose one of the following refueling options at the time of rental:

Self-Service Refueling:
Purchase fuel just prior to returning and return the car to Avis with a full tank of gas. If you choose this option, Avis will not charge you for fuel.

EZFuel and Fuel Service Charge:
Driving under 75 miles? With our newest refueling service, customers who drive less than 75 miles pay a low flat fee for fuel and return the car without refueling. We'll automatically charge you a flat fee of $13.99. If you present a receipt for the purchase of fuel, the charge will be removed at the time of return.

Please Note: Only the Fuel Service Option can be reserved online. Please select FSO on our Rental Options page. If you do not select the Fuel Service Option during your online reservation, you may choose a refueling option at the time of rental."

"more_info_debit_card_ios" : "Please spend a moment reviewing these important terms because Avis wants you to be delighted with your rental experience!

A reservation payment on Avis.com is a real-time transaction. Once you accept the terms and conditions, the card that is used to prepay this reservation will be immediately pre-authorized for the full amount of the estimated total charges along with a security deposit. Any unused funds secured on your credit or debit card will be released when you return the car and could take up to 10 business days to appear on your bank statement.

At the time of rental you will be required to present either the credit card or debit card used to make the â€œPay Nowâ€ reservation. There are certain restrictions on the use of the debit card for qualification to rent. Most U.S. locations will accept bank debit cards with the Visa or Mastercard logo if you are at least 25 years of age. At airport locations proof of a return flight that coincides with the rental must be shown. Debit cards are also not accepted when renting specialty vehicles. In most cases U.S. locations will perform a credit check for debit card renters to determine credit worthiness at the time of rental. If we are unable to complete the credit check or the credit check fails you should be prepared to present a major credit card in your own name.

Please Note: Debit cards may not be accepted at some Avis locations.

"roadside_safetynet_more_info" : "Your %1$s

The Avis Extended Roadside Assistance product provides the added reassurance of having roadside service for items that are not normally included in the cost of a rental such as key replacement, fuel delivery, lock out service, jump start assistance or tire change service.

A customer that accepts Extended Roadside Assistance can be assured that all of these services will be covered at no additional fee should they be needed. For example, if keys are locked in the car, Avis will provide the customer with a locksmith service to regain entry at no additional cost to the customer. In the event the customer has a dead battery, a service provider will be dispatched to assist at no additional cost to the customer.

Extended Roadside Assistance Terms & Conditions:
Taxes not included in the Estimated Total and will be applied at the time of rental.
Extended Roadside Assistance (ERA) service is available at all participating Avis locations in the U.S., Canada, Puerto Rico & U.S. Virgin Islands and New Zealand.
The daily/weekly fee for the AVIS Extended Roadside Assistance Option is subject to change.
ERA covers the cost for assistance with key replacement lockouts, tire change service fee, jump starts and emergency fuel delivery (up to 3 gallons).
Prohibited use of the vehicle will void this option."

"sli_more_info_us_ios" : "

Supplemental Liability Insurance (SLI) is excess automobile liability coverage that protects all authorized drivers of the rental vehicle against third-party bodily injury and property-damage claims up to a combined single limit of USD $1,000,000 or $2,000,000 depending on the rental location*. At some locations in states that do not require the car rental company to provide statutory minimum liability coverage, Supplemental Liability Insurance (SLI) will provide automobile liability coverage in excess of the State statutory minimums or your existing liability insurance coverage (whichever is greater), and it protects all authorized drivers of the rental vehicle against third-party bodily injury and property-damage claims up to USD $1,000,000 for your rental in the U.S.(excluding your injuries and your passengers' injuries) arising from your rental. Extra coverage means greater peace of mind. Next time you rent a car, be sure you're prepared for life's unexpected turns. This optional coverage offers you big peace of mind for a small investment.

* If you are renting in California or Nevada, please check with the Budget location for specific carrier, program terms/conditions, exclusions and/or limitations of coverage as these may differ from the SLI described above. We also advise you to consult with your individual insurer before rental.

Subject to the Avis Terms and Conditions.

* Pre-selected Options

If an option is checked and you can't deselect, then either: 1. You chose to include this option with your reservations when you selected your preferences in your RapidRez profile. If you want different protections for this reservation, you'll need to re-start this reservation. You can change your preferences online at any time and those preferences will automatically be applied to your future reservations. Or, 2. The option is included in the car rate that you selected.

"

"fso_more_info" : "Your %1$s

For your convenience, we offer several convenient refueling options:

Avis Fuel Service Option:
Save yourself time and frustration by adding our Fuel Service Option to your next online reservation. By selecting the Fuel Service Option, you can purchase a tank of gas directly from Avis at the time of rental, and avoid the hassle of searching for a gas station to fill the tank before returning the car.

If the Fuel Service Option isn’t exactly what you’re looking for, choose one of the following refueling options at the time of rental:

Self-Service Refueling:
Purchase fuel just prior to returning and return the car to Avis with a full tank of gas. If you choose this option, Avis will not charge you for fuel.

EZFuel and Fuel Service Charge:
Driving under 75 miles? With our newest refueling service, customers who drive less than 75 miles pay a low flat fee for fuel and return the car without refueling. We'll automatically charge you a flat fee of $13.99. If you present a receipt for the purchase of fuel, the charge will be removed at the time of return.

Please Note: Only the Fuel Service Option can be reserved online. Please select FSO on our Rental Options page. If you do not select the Fuel Service Option during your online reservation, you may choose a refueling option at the time of rental."

You can change your preferences on the Avis website or mobile app at any time, and those preferences will automatically be applied to your future reservations. Or,

2. The option is included in the car rate that you selected."

playstore_details.title: Avis Car Rental
playstore_details.description:
Need to rent a car on the go? The Avis Car Rental app has you covered. Exclusive to the Avis app, Avis Preferred members gain access to all features as well as exchanging or upgrading your car upon arriving at the rental location, quickly returning your car, locking and unlocking your car and more real-time rental features. Find your nearest Avis Car Rental locations, hours of operation, addresses and phone numbers at any time. 

Avis Preferred members can also earn points by opting in upon check out. With the Avis app, you can make, modify or cancel reservations 24/7. Using the Avis app will also provide access to getting a receipt, viewing and reviewing past rentals and contacting Roadside Assistance for immediate help. 

By tapping the Install button or by downloading the Avis App published by Avis Rent A Car System LLC, you consent to the installation of the Avis App and to its future updates and upgrades. You can withdraw your consent at any time by uninstalling the app. To request assistance with the removal or disabling of the Avis App, please contact us.

You acknowledge and understand and agree that the Avis App (including any updates or upgrades) may cause your device to automatically communicate with Avis’ servers to deliver the functionality described above and to record location-based information and usage metrics, (ii) affect app-related preferences or data stored in your device, and (iii) collect personal information as set out in our Privacy Notice at https://www.avis.com/privacy and in the Avis App Terms of Use at https://www.avis.com/mobiletou. The Avis App delivers push notifications. You may turn push notifications off in the “Preferences” tab.

Contact us at:
avis.com/mobilefeedback

Or contact us at 
Avis Rent A Car System LLC
Phone: 1-800-352-7900
Email: custserv@avis.com
Write: P.O. Box 699000
Tulsa, OK 74169-900
